The course lays the foundation for the rest of your studies in law. It aims to develop the skills that 
you need in order to study law effectively. It introduces you to the basics of the South African legal 
system (see below for the syllabus). The course will teach you how to read, think and write like a 
lawyer. Some of the main skills we teach include the ability to: 
- read and work with case law (judgments of the courts); 
- work with legislation (laws written by law-making bodies such as Parliament); 
- think critically in order to analyse and solve legal problems by applying the law; 
- use the library and electronic resources to research the law; and 
- develop and write clear and concise legal arguments.
